cs.CR, cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.IT, cs.SE

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper deals with the security of redactable blockchains and proposes a method based on the RSA encryption scheme. 
2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses the construction of redactable blockchains and proposes a method that can be used with any reasonable hash function. 
3. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper discusses the computational hardness of the RSA problem and the discrete logarithm problem, which are used to ensure public immutability and corruption resistance of the blockchain, respectively. 
4. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the use of hash functions in building blockchains and proposes a method that can be used with any reasonable hash function. 
5. cs.SE (Software Engineering) - The paper proposes a method for constructing redactable blockchains, which can have implications for software engineering and development of blockchain-based systems.
